The House Of Prayers
The peaceful, nice and overwhelming place the experience of visiting there is great.
I had celebrated Eid twice and many more Fridays  but never felt like I wasn't at my hometown.
Management is good specially (molana sahab) and others.
People of various countries came to pray on Friday
It feels different , I had never experienced these in any other places where I got to pray.
The people who came there were also nice I had asked them a couple of times for lift from mosque to busstand each time a new guy but same gesture
May Allah bless them with his never-ending blessings.
There is a guy "the surma guy"who sells (itr, surma, caps etc)  he can apply surma for you for free he never charges for it.
Insaallah,I hope the work of Mimar soon gets complete before I go there for next time.

Allah-u-akbar.

Having recently visited the mosque in my village, I am delighted to share my enchanting experience. Nestled in the heart of our community,        *SUNNIHABBIBMASJID* stands as a testament to the power of simplicity and the profound impact a local place of worship can have on its residents.

The modest yet elegant design of the mosque reflects the spirit of our village. Its unassuming exterior blends harmoniously with the surrounding landscape, creating a peaceful oasis amidst the hustle and bustle of everyday life. Stepping inside, I was greeted by a warm and inviting ambiance that instantly put me at ease.

Despite its size, the mosque exudes a sense of tranquility that is hard to find elsewhere. The intimate prayer hall creates an atmosphere of unity, bringing worshippers together in their devotion. The soft lighting and gentle aroma of incense create a serene setting, facilitating deep reflection and spiritual connection.

What truly sets *SUNNIHABBIBMASJID* apart is the tight-knit community it fosters. The mosque serves as a meeting place for locals to gather, not only for prayers but also for various events and social activities. It is a hub where neighbors come together, forging bonds of friendship and support. The sense of camaraderie and solidarity within the mosque's walls is truly heartwarming.

The mosque's dedicated volunteers and imams play an essential role in nurturing this community spirit. They are always available to guide and support worshippers, providing religious education and counseling when needed. Their warm and approachable nature makes everyone feel welcome and valued, fostering an environment of inclusivity and acceptance.

Although the mosque may be small in size, its impact on the lives of its residents is immeasurable. It serves as a center of learning, hosting regular lectures and study circles that enrich the spiritual knowledge of the community. It also acts as a beacon of compassion, organizing charitable initiatives and supporting those in need.

Visiting *SUNNIHABBIBMASJID* was a humbling experience that reminded me of the power of faith and the importance of community. It is a testament to the resilience and devotion of our village, and a source of inspiration for generations to come.

I wholeheartedly recommend exploring *SUNNIHABBIBMASJID* to both residents and visitors seeking a moment of solace and a glimpse into the authentic spirit of our village. It embodies the essence of a close-knit community, where faith, compassion, and unity intertwine to create an atmosphere of profound serenity.
